<TITLE> UEFA ban Scolari for last four Euro qualifiers </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 ZURICH, Sept 20 (bdnews24.com/Reuters) - UEFA have banned Portugal coach Luiz Felipe Scolari for four matches following his assault on Serbia player Ivica Dragutinovic, European soccer's governing body said on its Web site on Thursday. The punishment, announced by UEFA's disciplinary body, means Scolari will be unable to coach Portugal during their last four Euro 2008 qualifying matches. Scolari, who was also fined 12,000 euros ($16,780), lashed out at Dragutinovic following Portugal's 1-1 draw at home to Serbia on Sept 12. Dragutinovic, who was shown a red card at the end of the match, was given a two-match ban by UEFA for improper conduct. Portugal are third in Group A four points adrift of leaders Poland and two points behind Finland, although they have a game in hand on both countries. The top two qualify for the finals
